title: Florida - unemployment rate 1992 to 2018
summary: Overall Unemployment rate has increased over the Year.
Unemployment rate is roughly constant from '04 to '06, gradually increasing from '06 to '09, and finally roughly constant from '09 to '11.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year '08 and '09.
The highest Unemployment rate, of value 11.1 was reached at Year '10
Minimum Unemployment rate about 3.2 was reached at Year '06
